<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CHASSIS ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Air
        Dryer
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Air Dryer</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The thermal switch located in the air dryer should only close when the temperature is less than 10&#176;C
                    (50&#176;F), causing the air dryer heater to operate.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0823906" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Air Dryer</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.42in"/>
                <thead valign="bottom">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check 10A fuse F14 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F14</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then correct. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With key switch (24) in the ignition position, measure voltage at fuse F14, circuit
                                12A to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F14, 12A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (13). Turn key on and at circuit 39 (pin H4), measure voltage to
                                ground
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(13), 39 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 39, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (13), and disconnect conn. (79). Turn key on and measure voltage to
                                ground at black wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(79), black wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in black wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance between ground and the white wire of conn. (79).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(79), white wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in the white wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Install a test jumper wire between the black wire and terminal A of air dryer conn.
                                (79). Turn key on and measure voltage between terminal B of conn. (79) and white wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(79), term. B to white wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air dryer circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Service thermal switch/ heater assembly of air dryer.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
